\cpter{Prgrp}

Prgrps re te building blcks f ppers. A prgrp is defined s " grup f sentences r  single sentence tt frms  unit". Te unity nd cerence f ides mng sentences is wt cnstitutes  prgrp. Ultimtely,  prgrp is  sentence r grup f sentences tt supprt ne min ide, wic is referred t s te "cntrlling ide", becuse it cntrls wt ppens in te rest f te prgrp.

\sectin{Develpment}

Every prgrp in  pper suld be:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Unified: All f te sentences in  single prgrp suld be relted t  single cntrlling ide (ften expressed in te tpic sentence f te prgrp), nd te cntrlling ide suld refer t te centrl ide, r tesis, f te pper.
    \item Cerent: Te sentences suld be rrnged in  lgicl mnner nd suld fllw  definite pln fr develpment.
    \item Well-develped: Every ide discussed in te prgrp suld be dequtely explined nd supprted trug evidence nd detils tt wrk tgeter t explin te prgrp's cntrlling ide.
\end{itemize}

Orgnize  prgrp. Te rgniztin yu cse will depend n te cntrlling ide f te prgrp. Belw re  few pssibilities fr rgniztin:
\begin{itemize}[nsep]
    \item Nrrtin: Tell  stry. G crnlgiclly, frm strt t finis.
    \item Descriptin: Prvide specific detils. Orgnize sptilly, in rder f ppernce, r by tpic.
    \item Prcess: Explin w smeting wrks, step by step. Perps fllw  sequence -- first, secnd, tird.
    \item Clssifictin: Seprte int grups r explin te vrius prts f  tpic.
    \item Illustrtin: Give exmples nd explin w tse exmples prve yur pint. 
\end{itemize}

5-step prcess t prgrp develpment
\begin{enumerte}
    \item \emp{Decide n  cntrlling ide nd crete  tpic sentence}. Prgrp develpment begins wit te frmultin f te cntrlling ide. Tis ide directs te prgrp's develpment. Often, te cntrlling ide f  prgrp will pper in te frm f  tpic sentence, wic is used s n pening sttement t guide reders fr te rest f te prgrp. In sme cses, yu my need mre tn ne sentence t express  prgrp's cntrlling ide.
    \item \emp{Explin te cntrlling ide}. Prgrp develpment cntinues wit n expressin f te rtinle r te explntin tt te writer gives fr w te reder suld interpret te infrmtin presented in te ide sttement r tpic sentence f te prgrp. Te writer explins is/er tinking but te min tpic, ide, r fcus f te prgrp. 
    \item \emp{Give exmples}. Prgrp develpment prgresses wit te expressin f sme type f supprt r evidence fr te ide nd te explntin tt cme befre it. Te exmple serves s  sign r representtin f te reltinsip estblised in te ide nd explntin prtins f te prgrp.
    \item  \emp{Explin te exmples}. Te next mvement in prgrp develpment is n explntin f ec exmple nd its relevnce t te tpic sentence nd rtinle tt were stted t te beginning f te prgrp. Tis explntin sws reders wy yu cse t use tis/r tese prticulr exmples s evidence t supprt te mjr clim, r fcus, in yur prgrp. Cntinue te pttern f giving exmples nd explining tem until ll pints/exmples tt te writer deems necessry ve been mde nd explined. NONE f yur exmples suld be left unexplined.
    \item \emp{Cmplete te prgrp's ide r trnsitin int te next prgrp}. Te finl mvement in prgrp develpment invlves tying up te lse ends f te prgrp nd reminding te reder f te relevnce f te infrmtin in tis prgrp t te min r cntrlling ide f te pper. At tis pint, yu cn remind yur reder but te relevnce f te infrmtin tt yu just discussed in te prgrp. Yu migt feel mre cmfrtble, wever, simply trnsitining yur reder t te next develpment in te next prgrp.
\end{enumerte}

\sectin{Trnsitin}

Trnsitins cn elp reinfrce te underlying lgic f yur pper's rgniztin by prviding te reder wit essentil infrmtin regrding te reltinsip between yur ides. In tis wy, trnsitins ct s te glue tt binds te cmpnents f yur rgument r discussin int  unified, cerent, nd persusive wle.

\prgrp{Types f trnsitins}

Te types f trnsitins vilble t yu re s diverse s te circumstnces in wic yu need t use tem. A trnsitin cn be  single wrd,  prse,  sentence, r n entire prgrp. In ec cse, it functins te sme wy: first, te trnsitin eiter directly summrizes te cntent f  preceding sentence, prgrp, r sectin r implies suc  summry (by reminding te reder f wt s cme befre). Ten it elps te reder nticipte r cmpreend te new infrmtin tt yu wis t present.
\begin{itemize}
    \item Trnsitins between prgrps -- If yu ve dne  gd jb f rrnging prgrps s tt te cntent f ne leds lgiclly t te next, te trnsitin will igligt  reltinsip tt lredy exists by summrizing te previus prgrp nd suggesting smeting f te cntent f te prgrp tt fllws. A trnsitin between prgrps cn be  wrd r tw (wever, fr exmple, similrly),  prse, r  sentence. Trnsitins cn be t te end f te first prgrp, t te beginning f te secnd prgrp, r in bt plces.
    \item Trnsitins witin prgrps -- As wit trnsitins between sectins nd prgrps, trnsitins witin prgrps ct s cues by elping reders t nticipte wt is cming befre tey red it. Witin prgrps, trnsitins tend t be single wrds r srt prses.
\end{itemize}

Mke yur ides flw nd Keep yur reders n trck. Gd writers use  vriety f tecniques t crete unity nd cerence in teir prgrps nd sentences.
\begin{itemize}[nsep]
    \item Use n "ld-t-new" flw f infrmtin.
    \item Link by repetitin, but dn't verd it.
    \item Use prnuns t link t vid repetitin, but be creful tt te reference is cler t yur reder. Cutin! Te prnun "it" cn be very cnfusing fr yur reders. Use \emp{Referents(Tis/Tese) $+$  Nun Summry Prse} insted.
    \item Use synnyms t link.
    \item Mke cnnectins wit verbs (cllctins).
    \item Flw cnnectin nd trnsitin: use linking Wrds nd prses.
    \item Write cncisely nd trim unnecessry wrds.
\end{itemize}

\prgrp{Trnsitinl expressins}

Effectively cnstructing ec trnsitin ften depends upn yur bility t identify wrds r prses tt will indicte fr te reder te kind f lgicl reltinsips yu wnt t cnvey. Wenever yu ve truble finding  wrd, prse, r sentence t serve s n effective trnsitin, refer t reference resurces.

\sectin{Prprsing}

A prprse is  resttement (in yur wn wrds) f te ides in te riginl surce. Gd prprsing cn demnstrte tt yu ve understd te text yu ve red nd cn vid plgirizing.

\prgrp{Structured prprsing prcedure}
\begin{enumerte}[nsep]
    \item Fully understnd te riginl ides. Identify te imprtnt infrmtin in te surce nd te reltinsip between pints.
    \item Replce ec prt f te riginl surce wit crrespnding synnyms.
    \item Rewrite te mdified sentence by cnging te sentence structure, te vice, nd/r te wrd frms.
    \item Revise te prprse t utline te min ides nd key supprting detils. Imprve trnsitin nd infrmtin flw.
\end{enumerte}
